## BUGID_1: Rating below minimum is accepted (-1)
### Description
Negative rating is getting accepted in request payload (rating = -1)
### Steps to reproduce
1. POST to `/api/books`
2. Body:

{
  "title": "Tesssst Book",
  "author": "Testssss Author",
  "rating": -1
}
```
3. Observe response 
#### Example curl
```
{
  "title": "Blue Staaaar",
  "author": "Jane Doooooe",
  "rating": -1
}
```
### Expected
- 400 Bad Request
- No book created

### Actual
Response: 
{"title":"Blue Sssstar","author":"Jane Dosssse","genre":"Unknown","publishedYear":2026,"description":"No description available.","isbn":"N/A","pages":0,"rating":-1,"id":35}

### Suggested fix
- Add server-side validation
================================================================================================================================================

## BUGID_2: Rating above maximum is accepted (6)
- Labels: bug, backend, validation, high
- Severity: High

### Description
rating above the upper limit is getting accepted 

### Steps to reproduce
1. POST to `/api/books` with:
```json
{
  "title": "Test Book",
  "author": "Test Author",
  "rating": 6
}
```
```
### Expected
- 400 Bad Request
- Validation error: "rating must be between 0 and 5"

### Actual
{"url":"http://localhost:3000/api/books","status":201,"statusText":"Created","headers"}
======================================================================================================================================
