## BUGID_3: Client-supplied ID accepted on create

### Description
accepts a client-provided `id` and uses it when creating the record. ID generation should be server-side only.

### Steps to reproduce
1. POST to `/api/books` with:
```json
{
  "id": 222222,
  "title": "Test Book",
  "author": "Test Author"
}
```

#### Example curl
```
{
"id":2902,
"title":"ID Test Book",
"author":"ID Test Author"
}

```

### Expected
- 400 Bad Request or ignore `id` field
- Server assigns ID
-

### Actual
ID accepted and book created {"title":"ID Test Book","author":"ID Test Author","genre":"Unknown","publishedYear":2026,"description":"No description available.","isbn":"N/A","pages":0,"rating":0,"id":39}
UI http://localhost:3000/book/39

### Suggested fix
- Reject requests containing `id` with 400
================================================================================================================================================

